article.headline: Weber St. 69, Montana St. 61
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Davion Berry had 21 points, dished out five assists and grabbed four rebounds to lead Weber State to its sixth straight victory and a 69-61 win over Montana State on Saturday night. Jordan Richardson scored 16 points, Frank Otis chipped in with 14 points and five rebounds and the Wildcats shot 64.1 percent from the field, making 25 of 39 attempts. Weber State (19-5, 14-2 Big Sky) hit 6 of 12 from 3-point range and was 13 of 16 from the free-throw line. Weber State led 35-30 at halftime but used a 20-9 run to begin the second half to put the Bobcats away. Marcus Colbert scored 19 points, pulled five rebounds and had three assists to lead Montana State (10-14, 7-9), which shot 40 percent from the field and hit nine 3-pointers. Paul Egwuonwu had 12 points and six rebounds while Christian Moon added 15.
